## Folder Structure

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `agent_v2/` lives **inside** `backend/app/` so Python can find it. `pyproject.toml` only packages `app.*` ([lines 46-48](file:///Users/adarshmaurya/Downloads/Projects/inquira-ce/backend/pyproject.toml#L46-L48)), so a repo-root `agent_v2/` would fail at import time.

```
backend/app/
  agent/                         ← OLD agent (kept until cleanup)
    graph.py
    code_guard.py
  agent_v2/                      ← NEW — self-contained, importable as app.agent_v2
    __init__.py                  ← exports build_graph()
    graph.py                     ← ReAct StateGraph
    state.py                     ← InputSchema, OutputSchema, AgentState
    router.py                    ← single-call router (with tool access)
    nodes.py                     ← react_loop, chat, reject, finalize
    tools/
      __init__.py
      inspect_schema.py
      sample_data.py
      bash_tool.py
      execute_python.py
      pip_install.py
      finish_analysis.py
    prompts/
      router_system.yaml
      react_system.yaml
      general_chat_system.yaml
    memory/
      summarizer.py
```

### Registry Wired Into Actual Graph Loader

Currently `WorkspaceLangGraphManager` ([line 15](file:///Users/adarshmaurya/Downloads/Projects/inquira-ce/backend/app/v1/services/langgraph_workspace_manager.py#L15)) hard-imports `from ...agent.graph import build_graph`. This is the **only place** the graph is loaded at runtime.

**Fix:** Change `WorkspaceLangGraphManager.get_graph()` to use the registry:

```python
# backend/app/agent/registry.py
from ..core.config import load_config

def get_build_graph_fn():
    version = load_config().agent.version  # "agent_v2"
    if version == "agent_v2":
        from ..agent_v2 import build_graph
        return build_graph
    from ..agent.graph import build_graph  # legacy fallback
    return build_graph
```

```python
# langgraph_workspace_manager.py — MODIFIED
-from ...agent.graph import build_graph
+from ...agent.registry import get_build_graph_fn

class WorkspaceLangGraphManager:
    async def get_graph(self, workspace_id, agent_memory_path):
        ...
-       graph = build_graph(checkpointer=checkpointer)
+       build_graph = get_build_graph_fn()
+       graph = build_graph(checkpointer=checkpointer)
        ...
```

